ce:section.ce:para:
Herein, we report glutathione (GSH)-templated bimetallic copper-cerium nanoclusters (Cu/Ce NCs), dispersed in isopropanol (IPA)/PB mixed solution, can be self-assembled to non-fluorescent nanowire network. Further, unexpectedly, the Cu/Ce NCs dispersed in 60% (v/v) IPA/phosphate buffer (PB, 10 mM, pH7.0) mixed solution can be greatly triggered red fluorescence turn-on by Cys, along with nanowire network aggregated to blocky structure (
                     Scheme 1
                     ). Based on this, a simple, selective and sensitive fluorimetric sensor for Cys was developed. To the best of our knowledge, this work may report for the first time that the self-assembly of bimetallic NCs aggregated into nanowire network, further exhibited strong red fluorescence emission triggered by Cys along with the formation of blocky structure.
